stories.text:
Is time getting quicker but I feel like it was just the other day everyone could not stop talking about the 'newest' emerging technologies we MUST all jump in on. IOT and Big Data.

Just curious what every came from the hype, or did we all just realise we didn't want out garbage cans communicating with our refrigerators and companies realised maybe there is such thing as too much information?

Was it all just replaced with the ever more important blockchain hype..
